oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Bob Wills Live at the S. and S. Club - 1956-02-29 - Reel 2
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The recording is of Bob Wills (musician) live in the S. and S. Club. The performance is accompanied by Texas Playboys: Louie Tierney (fiddle and saxophone), Luke Wills (bass), Joe Andrews (vocal and bass), Millard Kelso (piano), Billy Bowman (steel guitar), Johnny Dalton (drums), and Lou Walker (unidentified). The recording is from February 25, 1956. The tape is labeled reel two.
